-- Deutsche Boerse plans no convertible bond issue now
-- By Jonathan Gould
-- Tue Apr 29, 2014 08:42AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, April 29 (Reuters) - Deutsche Boerse <DB1Gn.DE> has no plans to issue convertible bonds at this stage, its Chief Financial Officer Gregor Pottmeyer told a conference call on Tuesday.

The German exchange operator has asked its shareholders for permission to issue convertible bonds, which can be converted into equity capital, as an additional potential financing alternative.